rganisation)|Momentum]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/labour-leadership-rebecca-long-bailey-momentum-election-corbyn-a9286666.html|title=Labour leadership: Rebecca Long-Bailey endorsed by Momentum in race to succeed Corbyn|date=16 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020|work=The Independent|first=Ashley|last=Cowburn}}</ref>\n* [[Maxine Peake]], actress<ref>{{cite news |last= Hopkins |first= Daniel |date= 29 January 2020 |title= Actress Maxine Peake voices support for Rebecca Long-Bailey |url= https://www.salfordcitynews.co.uk/news/18194993.actress-maxine-peake-voices-support-rebecca-long-bailey/ |work= Salford City News |access-date= 6 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Serwotka]], leader of the [[Public and Commercial Services Union|PCS]] trade union<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/feb/06/failing-to-elect-long-bailey-risks-return-to-2015-union-chief-tells-labour|title=Failing to elect Long-Bailey risks return to 2015, union chief tells Labour|last=Syal|first=Rajeev|date=6 February 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=6 February 2020|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n=== Lisa Nandy ===\n* [[Tom Copley]], [[London Assembly]] member<ref name=\"Nandy-letter\"/>\n* [[Tony Cunningham]], former MP for [[Workington (UK Parliament constituency)|Workington]] and former minister<ref name=\"Nandy-letter\">{{Cite web|url=https://labourlist.org/2020/01/open-letter-lisa-nandy-as-leader-can-end-in-fighting-with-vision-for-real-change/|title=Open letter: Nandy as leader can \"end in-fighting\" with \"vision for real change\"|last=Rodgers|first=Sienna|date=11 January 2020|work=LabourList|access-date=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Peter Hain]], Labour peer, former MP for [[Neath (UK Parliament constituency)|Neath]] and former minister<ref name=\"Nandy-letter\"/>\n* [[Ian McCartney]], former MP for [[Makerfield (UK Parliament constituency)|Makerfield]]<ref name=\"Nandy-letter\"/>\n* [[Melanie Onn]], former MP for [[Great Grimsby (UK Parliament constituency)|Great Grimsby]] (''previously endorsed [[Jess Phillips]]'')<ref>{{cite news |last1=Corkon |first1=Jon |title=Who former Grimsby MP Melanie Onn is backing as next Labour leader |url=https://www.grimsbytelegraph.co.uk/news/who-former-grimsby-mp-melanie-3769135 |accessdate=12 March 2020 |publisher=Grimsby Live |date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Jack McConnell]], Labour peer and former [[First Minister of Scotland|first minister of Scotland]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/fp/news/politics/westminster/1942805/ex-first-minister-jack-mcconnell-accuses-labour-leadership-candidate-of-giving-up-on-scotland/|title=Ex-First Minister Jack McConnell accuses Labour leadership candidate of 'giving up' on Scotland|work=The Press and Journal|last=O'Donoghue|first=Daniel|date=10 January 2020|access-date= 16 January 2020|publisher=DC Thomson Media}}</ref>\n* [[George Monbiot]], writer and environmental and political activist<ref>{{cite tweet|user=BBCPolitics |number=1233376636621541378 |date=28 February 2020 |title=Lisa Nandy would be my favourite\u201d for Labour leader says writer George Monbiot, \u201cshe\u2019s got a lovely touch, she gets the collaborative nature of what politics now needs to be}}</ref>\n* [[Estelle Morris]], Labour peer, former MP for [[Birmingham Yardley (UK Parliament constituency)|Birmingham Yardley]] and former minister<ref name=\"Nandy-letter\"/>\n* [[Catherine McKinnell]], Labour MP for [[Newcastle upon Tyne North (UK Parliament constituency)|Newcastle upon Tyne North]] (''previously endorsed [[Jess Phillips]]'')<ref>{{cite news |last1=McKinnell |first1=Catherine |title=Why I\u2019m backing Lisa Nandy to be Labour\u2019s next leader |url=https://labourlist.org/2020/02/catherine-mckinnell-why-im-backing-lisa-nandy-for-leader/ |accessdate=12 March 2020 |work=LabourList|date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Ann Taylor, Baroness Taylor of Bolton|Ann Taylor]], Labour peer, former MP for [[Dewsbury (UK Parliament cons