cessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Jack Sargeant (politician)|Jack Sargeant]], AM for [[Alyn and Deeside (Assembly constituency)|Alyn and Deeside]]<ref name=\"carwyn\"/>\n* [[Ricky Tomlinson]], actor<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/ricky-tomlinson-slams-boris-buffoon-17587807|title=Ricky Tomlinson slams 'Boris the buffoon' and backs Keir Starmer|last=Thorp|first=Liam|date=17 January 2020|work=Liverpool Echo|access-date=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Withdrawn candidates ===\nClive Lewis was endorsed by the journalist and broadcaster [[Paul Mason (journalist)|Paul Mason]] before he withdrew.<ref name=\"Paul Mason\" /> Before she withdrew, Jess Phillips was endorsed by the journalist [[Matthew d'Ancona]], the Labour peer [[Philip Hunt, Baron Hunt of Kings Heath|Philip Hunt]] and [[Melanie Onn]], the former MP  for [[Great Grimsby (UK Parliament constituency)|Great Grimsby]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/comment/comment/talented-strong-and-relatable-jess-phillips-is-labour-s-best-asset-a4316766.html|title=Talented, strong and relatable \u2014 Jess Phillips is Labour's best asset|last=d'Ancona|first=Matthew|date=18 December 2019|work=Evening Standard|accessdate=19 December 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Guardian-Phillips\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/jan/03/jess-phillips-poised-to-enter-labour-leadership-contest|title=Jess Phillips confirms she will stand for Labour leadership|last=Stewart|first=Heather|date=3 January 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=5 January 2020|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/politics/former-grimsby-mp-melanie-onn-backs-jess-phillips-for-next-labour-leader-1-10182151|title=Former Grimsby MP Melanie Onn backs Jess Phillips for next Labour leader|last=Scott|first=Geraldine|date=3 January 2020|work=Yorkshire Post|access-date=4 January 2020|publisher=JPI Media}}</ref>\n\n==Opinion polls==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"t